ontologyFramework.OFDataMapping.ReservatedDataType

Class EventComputeLowMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • ontologyFramework.OFDataMapping.ReservatedDataType.EventComputeLowMapper

  • public class EventComputeLowMapper
extends java.lang.Object
    This static class is used to implement mapper that are by default used from the framework; at least during start up. For this reason it works only unidirectionally from the ontology to the framework. In particular, It maps, separately, every part that describe the top abstraction description of an ontological Event. This must be an individual, for instance I, that contains data properties, as for example: I {@value #EVENTCOMPUTATIONLOW_propName} "risult1 && result2"^^string. Where the function thanks to which the events is evaluated can be written w.r.t to the limitation given by the implementation of OFEventInterface. Moreover, the variables: result1 and result2 must be defined in the same individual as: I hasEventAggregation_result1 Ev_Event1Individual
    I hasEventAggregation_result2 Ev_Event2Individual.
    and they can be defined by any string. This relation is done to give the possibility to collect more event in unique boolean result.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Buoncomapgni Luca
